  "text": "Firefox DOM event dispatch is coordinated by the EventDispatcher class, which implements the DOM Event Standard's event dispatch algorithm. The dispatch chain consists of five key components:\n\n## 1. Event Creation (dom/events/EventDispatcher.h/cpp, dom/events/Event.h/cpp)\nThe process begins in `EventDispatcher::Dispatch()` (dom/events/EventDispatcher.cpp:869), which is the main entry point for event dispatch. If needed, `EventDispatcher::CreateEvent()` (dom/events/EventDispatcher.h:380) creates a DOM Event object from a WidgetEvent. The Event class (dom/events/Event.cpp) represents the public DOM event interface and stores event properties like type, target, phase, and timestamp.\n\n## 2. Event Target Identification (dom/base/FragmentOrElement.cpp, dom/base/nsIContent.h)\nThe event target chain is built by calling `GetEventTargetParent()` on each target in the hierarchy. The base implementation is in `nsIContent::GetEventTargetParent()` (dom/base/FragmentOrElement.cpp:799), which determines:\n  - Whether the current content can handle the event (mCanHandle flag)\n  - The parent target for propagation (shadow DOM slots, normal parent, or null)\n  - Event retargeting requirements across shadow DOM boundaries\n  - Special handling for mouseover/mouseout and pointer events with related targets\n\nElement-specific implementations exist in dom/base/Element.cpp for link handling via `Element::GetEventTargetParentForLinks()` (dom/base/Element.cpp:4217).\n\n## 3. Capture/Bubble Phase Traversal (dom/events/EventDispatcher.cpp)\nOnce the event target chain is built, `EventTargetChainItem::HandleEventTargetChain()` (dom/events/EventDispatcher.cpp:299) executes the three phases:\n  - **Capture Phase** (lines 516-585): Iterates from root to target, checking mInCapturePhase flag, calling listeners with capture=true\n  - **Target Phase** (lines 587-611): Dispatches to the actual event target (eMouseUp, eMouseDown, eClick, etc.) with both capture and bubbling listeners\n  - **Bubble Phase** (lines 613-648): Iterates from target back to root if mBubbles is true, calling bubbling listeners\n\nThe EventChainPreVisitor and EventChainPostVisitor classes (dom/events/EventDispatcher.h:53-323) manage phase state, propagation flags, and event retargeting information throughout dispatch.\n\n## 4. Event Listener Invocation (dom/events/EventListenerManager.h/cpp, dom/events/EventTarget.cpp)\nFor each event target in the chain, `EventTargetChainItem::HandleEvent()` (dom/events/EventDispatcher.cpp:339) retrieves the EventListenerManager and calls its `HandleEvent()` method (dom/events/EventListenerManager.h:435). The EventListenerManager:\n  - Checks listener applicability based on capture/bubbling phase and event flags\n  - Iterates through registered listeners via `HandleEventWithListenerArray()` (dom/events/EventListenerManager.cpp:1536)\n  - Invokes individual listeners through `HandleEventSingleListener()` (dom/events/EventListenerManager.cpp:1233)\n  - Handles both WebIDL callbacks and XPCOM listener interfaces\n  - Manages passive listeners, once listeners, and system group listeners\n\nListeners are registered via `EventTarget::AddEventListener()` (dom/events/EventTarget.cpp:90-105), which delegates to EventListenerManager for storage and retrieval.\n\n## 5. Default Action Execution (dom/events/EventStateManager.h/cpp, dom/base/Element.cpp, dom/html/HTMLInputElement.cpp)\nAfter listener invocation, default actions are executed in the system group via `PostHandleEvent()` implementations:\n  - `EventStateManager::PostHandleEvent()` (dom/events/EventStateManager.h:254) handles system-wide default actions for mouse, keyboard, and wheel events\n  - `Element::PostHandleEventForLinks()` (dom/base/Element.cpp:4318) handles navigation for anchor elements\n  - `HTMLInputElement::PostHandleEvent()` (dom/html/HTMLInputElement.cpp:3896) handles form submission, checkbox/radio state changes, and range input updates\n\nDefault actions only execute if `preventDefault()` was not called (checked via mCancelable flag). The system group dispatch (lines 651-693 in EventDispatcher.cpp) allows system code to perform default actions after content listeners have run.\n\n## Complete Dispatch Sequence\n1. EventDispatcher::Dispatch() called with target and WidgetEvent\n2. Event target chain built via GetEventTargetParent() traversal\n3. EventChainPreVisitor set up with initial event state\n4. PreHandleEvent() called on all chain items\n5. HandleEventTargetChain() executes:\n   - Capture phase: root to target, calling capture=true listeners\n   - Target phase: target element with both capture and bubble listeners\n   - Bubble phase: target to root, calling capture=false listeners\n6. For each phase and target, EventListenerManager::HandleEvent() invokes listeners\n7. After default group dispatch, system group dispatch occurs\n8. PostHandleEvent() executes default actions if not prevented\n9. Event propagation complete, results returned to caller"
}

